In the MATTER OF Francis C. BABCOCK, Jr., An Attorney At Law (Attorney No. 009791990) M-1281 September Term 2018
D-135-18
082980 Supreme Court of New Jersey. July 11, 2019

ORDER

This matter having been duly presented on the motion for reinstatement to practice filed by Francis C. Babcock, Jr., of Jersey City, who was admitted to the bar of this State in 1990, and who has been temporarily suspended from the practice of law since July 8, 2019;

And the Disciplinary Review Board having reported to the Court that respondent has paid the outstanding administrative costs owed;

And good cause appearing;

It is ORDERED that the motion is granted, and Francis C. Babcock, Jr., is reinstated to the practice of law, effective immediately.
